list.item:
Gather the supplies you will need for your injection (


                           Figure B
                        ).

Check the expiration (Exp) date on the vial label (


                                       Figure C
                                    ).

If using a new vial, remove the plastic cap (


                                       Figure E
                                    ) and throw away this plastic cap in the trash. Do not put the plastic cap back on the vial.

Clean the top of the vial rubber stopper with 1 alcohol wipe (


                                       Figure F
                                    ). Throw away the alcohol wipe in the trash.

td.paragraph:
When measuring your dose, be sure to read the markings starting from the end closest to the black rubber stopper (


                                    Figure G
                                 ).

list.item:
With 1 hand, pinch about 2 inches of skin at the injection site between your thumb and index (pointer) finger (


                                       Figure P
                                    ). Pinching the skin is important to help make sure that you inject the medicine under the skin (into fatty tissue) but not any deeper (into the muscle).

Hold the middle of the syringe (where the markings are printed) at a 90-degree angle to your body and push the needle straight into the injection site (


                                       Figure Q
                                    ). Make sure that you push the needle all the way into the skin.

Slowly push the plunger down to inject the medicine (


                                       Figure R
                                    )
